        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1151234330" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1218514451757939730">For years I avoided Barnes: I blame Martin Amis and Ian McEwan for reaching a point in their career where they were just marking time, and my stupidity for lumping Barnes in with them. Plus, the subject matter: it&apos;s fair to assume that maybe this is a gap-filler, a publisher suggestion for an idea-impoverished author etc.<br/><br/>Happily, this is Barnes&apos; best book, of those things of his I finally got round to. He is the best of that generation of English writers, I think. Stylistically he is peerless. P</span>
  <span id="freeText1218514451757939730" style="display:none">For years I avoided Barnes: I blame Martin Amis and Ian McEwan for reaching a point in their career where they were just marking time, and my stupidity for lumping Barnes in with them. Plus, the subject matter: it's fair to assume that maybe this is a gap-filler, a publisher suggestion for an idea-impoverished author etc.<br /><br />Happily, this is Barnes' best book, of those things of his I finally got round to. He is the best of that generation of English writers, I think. Stylistically he is peerless. Predictably, it's meandering, but I'm not averse to digressive ruminations, and done this well...Barnes can render everything, even our mutual mortality, funny, charming and joyous. A fantastic piece of work.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1218514451757939730" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
