  <span id="freeText17887305411578108824" style="display:none">I sense a strange incongruency. My date for reading this book on Goodreads is May 2010 yet I distinctly recall reading this at Halloween the first year we lived in our house. I also recall reading one of the anecdotes to two friends, one of whom died shortly thereafter from cancer. I still think of Barnes chiding his final reader and smile. I am struggling today, keeping matters in a certain order when my impulse is to flee. We are on holiday next week and I am working quite a bit before then and I find it irrelevant to parse the causes of my dysfunction.</span>
